    <briefdescription>
<para>A surface manager that ensures that only allows a fixed, exclusive set of child surfaces. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This is a convenience subclass for composition patterns: <computeroutput> class MySurface : public <ref refid="classerbsland_1_1cterm_1_1ui_1_1_surface" kindref="compound">Surface</ref>, protected <ref refid="classerbsland_1_1cterm_1_1ui_1_1_exclusive_surface_manager" kindref="compound">ExclusiveSurfaceManager</ref> { public: [[nodiscard]] static MySurfacePtr create() { auto result = std::make_shared&lt;MySurface&gt;(); result-&gt;initializeUi(); return result; } protected: bool <ref refid="classerbsland_1_1cterm_1_1ui_1_1_exclusive_surface_manager_1ae81b10c79d08a3cd9f686aea3475c5c8" kindref="member">isManagedChild(const SurfacePtr &amp;surface) const </ref>noexcept { return surface == _managedChild; } private: void initializeUi() { _managedChild = <ref refid="classerbsland_1_1cterm_1_1ui_1_1surface_1_1_text_box_1a7cac243451bd95ed3f90c9f4c17f07c3" kindref="member">TextBox::create()</ref>; childStorage().add(_managedChild); // works! } private: TextBoxPtr _managedChild; }; </computeroutput> </para>
    </detaileddescription>
